# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Bede Homeschool Tutor — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in every value before running.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   nano .env          ← or use any editor
#   make start
#
# SECURITY: .env is in .gitignore and must NEVER be committed.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Claude API ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get yours at: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ── Bede's spoken voice (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenAI TTS — cloud API, small per-character cost, meaningfully more
# natural than a browser's default voice. See docs/VOICE_SETUP.md for full
# setup. Leave unset to fall back to the browser's own built-in speech —
# voice output is always optional.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...
# OPENAI_TTS_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini-tts
# OPENAI_TTS_VOICE=fable

# ── Post-session diagnostic email (optional) ─────────────────────────────────
# Lets a parent get Bede's end-of-session notes emailed to them once via
# Resend (resend.com). The address is never written to the database or the
# audit log. Leave RESEND_API_KEY unset to disable this feature entirely.
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
# RESEND_FROM_ADDRESS=Bede <bede@yourdomain.com>

# ── Distress alert (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Urgent email to the parent when Bede detects a child in distress or danger
# and pauses the session. Reuses the Resend setup above. Child-triggered, so
# it needs an address set ahead of time (unlike the diagnostic email, which
# is typed in at send time). The safeguarding event is always recorded in the
# encrypted audit log regardless — this adds a real-time alert on top of
# that. Leave unset to disable this specific alert.
# PARENT_EMAIL=parent@example.com

# ── Beta feedback (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Routes CX/UX/content-quality feedback submitted via POST /feedback to your
# own inbox — reuses the Resend setup above. Deliberately separate from
# PARENT_EMAIL (a family's own address): this is the operator's address, for
# beta testing feedback from parents, children, and public demo visitors
# alike. Leave unset to disable the feature entirely (returns 404).
# FEEDBACK_EMAIL=you@example.com

# ── Secrets (generate with: openssl rand -hex 32) ────────────────────────────
# JWT signing key — used to sign parent/child login tokens
SECRET_KEY=replace-me-openssl-rand-hex-32

# Encryption master secret — used to derive the AES-256-GCM data key.
# IMPORTANT: Changing this after first run WILL make all stored data unreadable.
MASTER_SECRET=replace-me-openssl-rand-hex-32

# ── Access credentials ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Parent password — used to log in as the administrator role
PARENT_PASSWORD=choose-a-strong-passphrase

# Child PIN — used by the student to log in.
# Must be 6+ digits and not an easily-guessable pattern: no sequential run
# (123456, 654321), repeated block (111111, 123123, 121212), or palindrome
# (669966). Repeated digits are otherwise fine, e.g. 602656 is a good PIN.
# Enforced at startup when PRODUCTION=true.
CHILD_PIN=602656

# ── Public demo mode (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only for a dedicated public demo deployment (see demo/), never a family's
# real instance. Leave unset to disable the demo entirely. Must differ from
# PARENT_PASSWORD and CHILD_PIN. Not a credential anyone types — purely the
# on/off switch; visitors log in via a self-service one-time code instead,
# which can only reach a fixed, read-mostly tutoring session — no
# configuration rights.
# DEMO_PIN=
# DEMO_CODE_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=120
# DEMO_STUDENT_NAME=Guest
# DEMO_GRADE=4
# DEMO_GRADE_STAGE=3-5

# ── Sandbox mode (optional, parent-only) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Unlocks a direct-answer "Ask Bede" chat for you (the parent) to test and
# explore how Bede responds — no Socratic-only rule, free topic-switching,
# and nothing said there is ever saved to the database. Not a separate
# login: it requires you to already be logged in as parent, plus this PIN
# on every request. Leave unset to disable entirely (default). Same
# strength rules as CHILD_PIN, and must differ from PARENT_PASSWORD,
# CHILD_PIN, and DEMO_PIN.
# SANDBOX_PIN=

# ── Parent MFA: FIDO2 security key (YubiKey, etc.) + TOTP (optional) ──────────
# Adds an optional second step at parent login, on top of PARENT_PASSWORD,
# once enrolled from the setup screen. TOTP needs nothing here — it's always
# available. Security keys need WEBAUTHN_RP_ID set — leave it blank to disable
# that option entirely (default). RP_ID must be the exact domain (no
# scheme/port) tablets/browsers use to reach this deployment, e.g. bede.local;
# ORIGIN is the full origin, e.g. https://bede.local. WebAuthn refuses to
# verify if either doesn't match exactly what the browser sees.
# WEBAUTHN_RP_ID=
# WEBAUTHN_RP_NAME=Bede
# WEBAUTHN_ORIGIN=
# TOTP_ISSUER=Bede Homeschool

# ── Database ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Two options — make setup asks which you want and fills this in for you;
# see docs/PRODUCTION_SETUP.md for the tradeoffs.
#
# Option 1: local Postgres (runs in Docker alongside Bede, no external
# account — see the "Storage model" comment in docker-compose.yml):
# COMPOSE_PROFILES=local-db
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=replace-me-openssl-rand-hex-24
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://sage:replace-me-openssl-rand-hex-24@db:5432/bede
#
# Option 2: managed Postgres (Neon, Supabase, Railway, etc.) — leave
# COMPOSE_PROFILES/POSTGRES_PASSWORD unset, set DATABASE_URL to your
# provider's connection string. A plain postgres:// or postgresql:// URL
# (what most providers hand you) is normalized automatically — no need to
# hand-edit in the +asyncpg driver suffix.
#
# Neon free tier example:
#   postgresql+asyncpg://sage:pass@ep-cool-name-123456.us-east-2.aws.neon.tech/sagedb?ssl=require
#
# Supabase example:
#   postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:pass@db.abcdefgh.supabase.co:5432/postgres?ssl=require
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://user:password@host/dbname?ssl=require

# ── Optional: override defaults ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# setup.sh auto-detects your LAN IP and sets CORS_ORIGINS for you.
# If you add tablets later, append their IP to the list:
# CORS_ORIGINS=https://localhost,https://192.168.1.100,https://192.168.1.101,http://ui:80
CORS_ORIGINS=https://localhost,http://ui:80
# DISABLE_API_DOCS=true
# PRODUCTION=true
